Statistical testing¶

Cure rate Testing¶

Null Hypothesis¶

A null hypothesis is a theory that assumes there is no statistical importance between the two variables in the hypothesis.¶

H0 - mean of states cure rate are significant, H1 - mean of states cure rate are not significant

Significant rate: 0.05

Both states Tamil Nadu & Kerala have no significant difference in Cure rate
Both states Tamil Nadu & Maharashtra have significant difference in Cure rate
Both states Kerala & Maharashtra have significant difference in Cure rate
the difference is becuase of high active cases? Lets do another test¶

Statistical function - scipy.stats¶

regression, linear models, time series analysis, extensions to topics also covered by scipy.stats.

scipy.stats.norm¶

A normal continuous random variable.

The location (loc) keyword specifies the mean. The scale (scale) keyword specifies the standard deviation.

As an instance of the rv_continuous class, norm object inherits from it a collection of generic methods (see below for the full list), and completes them with details specific for this particular distribution.
